As a way to provide greater convenience advantages for customers that are using PEM-based CA certs and keys for SSL, please consider including APR listeners in Confluence's {{server.xml}} file, similar to what is provided within JIRA. For example, the following listener can make it easier to configure SSL in certain situations:

{code}
<Listener className="org.apache.catalina.core.AprLifecycleListener" SSLEngine="on" />
{code}

