Government and other organizations in highly classified environments who need to include classification notices on emails do not want to add the classification notice to every email. Every email with the classified notice has to be treated as classified and this does not apply to most of the notifications of changes in Confluence.

If the entire page could be included in the email rather than just the changes then the notice could be on the classified pages (but not on the unclassified ones). This would enable the administrator to include the classified notice when classified pages are changed but not on the majority of notification emails.

